2.00	Everett_Alvarez	Everett Alvarez, Jr.	Everett Alvarez Jr. (b. 1937, Salinas, California) was a Navy Commander who endured one of the longest periods as a prisoner of war (POW) in American history. Alvarez was the first American pilot to be shot down and held as a POW in North Vietnam. He spent over 8 years in captivity, making him the second longest-held POW in American history. .	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c6/LCDR_Alvarez.jpg/200px-LCDR_Alvarez.jpg
